Communicated by:
ProMED

[Such cases are rare but not unknown. If the climate is suitable and the local _Anopheles_ mosquitoes are able to transmit malaria, it may be an infection from a person with a recent travel history to a malaria-endemic country; as in this case, Mozambique.

Other cases are more obscure like the case ProMED recently reported from Spain (see below) and a case from Italy where genetic analysis found the same strain of _P. falciparum_ in an Italian girl and a patient from Burkina Faso admitted to the same hospital. The route of transmission was never established. An analysis from the ECDC in 2018 listed 6 cases, mostly transfusion related. - Mod.EP

